<h1>Maximum upslope flowpath length</h1>

<p>
This tool calculates the maximum length of the flowpaths that run through each grid cell (in map horizontal units) in a flow pointer grid. The user must specify the name of a flow pointer grid derived using the <a href="FlowPointerD8.html">D8 flow algorithm</a> and the output raster image.</p>
<p>A temporary image is created during the operation of this tool. This temporary images should be automatically deleted upon successful completion. <b><i>NoData</b></i> valued grid cells in the input pointer image will be assigned <b><i>NoData</b></i> values in the output image. The output raster is of the <i>float</i> data type and <i>continuous</i> data scale.</p>


